name: Hiski Salomaa

He moved to Michigan's Upper Peninsula, where he made his living as a tailor. He was an advocate of syndicalism and joined the trade union "Industrial Workers of the World". His depiction of Finnish immigrant life was very popular  and an interesting feature of his writing was the use of "Finglish" making his lyrics difficult to understand outside of a Finnish-American or Finnish-Canadian setting. He is sometimes referred to as the Finnish Woody Guthrie.

Most notably he won three gold medals at the 1988 Winter Olympics in Calgary becoming - along with the speedskater Yvonne van Gennip of The Netherlands - the most successful athlete at that event. Since the 1990s, Nykänen's status as a celebrity was mainly fueled by his colourful personal relationships, his career as a pop singer and various incidents often related to heavy use of alcohol and violent behaviour.
